9. When bucket will be same/different in HashMap?
Answer:
Same bucket → same index (hash collision).
Different bucket → different index.
Index depends on hashCode and capacity.
Example: Same hash % capacity → same bucket.

10. How to calculate hash key (index)?
Answer:
HashMap uses:
index = (n - 1) & hash(key)
Where n = array size (power of 2).
Bitwise AND is faster than modulo.
Example: hash=10, n=16 → index = 10 & 15 = 10
